  "notes": "Vital Stats Mortality, MMR family ('a' sheets Q1a-Q4a). Split-config sibling of morta_imr (same physical workbook, second sheet family). 5 rows: NIR region rollup + 3 provinces + City of Bacolod HUC — province/HUC granularity only (FLAG M3). 13 raw inputs; every Total and Ratio column recomputed from raw (never trusted): col 33's header label wrongly says 'd4/a3' but the formula is verified g4/a3 (Indirect combined) — mapped by index per FLAG M1. Rates stored ALREADY MULTIPLIED (x100,000, ADR-023); the file's IFERROR(...,0) zero-fill is replaced by our null-on-missing-denominator convention. Annual1 sheet is a pure SUM rollup of Q1a-Q4a — not ingested; annual views aggregate quarterly data. Known DOH label cleanups pending: col 33 d4->g4, stale a1/a2 references (FLAG M2). Reconciliation DQC (direct+indirect=combined) pending the D4 rule type."
